{"event_id":"ev_01KX8ZB5HQ1KYVRZW84YRYJSYX","type":"code_review_failed","change_id":"review-contract-compiler","timestamp":"2026-07-11T16:14:37.111479Z","actor":{"type":"human","identifier":"dawinialo@163.com"},"framework":"plain","framework_state":null,"payload":{"reviewer":"code-reviewer","reason":"Scoped external review found participant, freshness, and lifecycle-state soundness gaps.","source":"external","verdict":{"verdict":"reject","bundle_digest":"5480dd5d545aed8d4373df327c678f4b787f7c7ea8b7f3331575f93476ce9c0d","checklist":[{"item":"spec-compliance","status":"fail"},{"item":"scope-adherence","status":"pass"},{"item":"code-quality","status":"fail"},{"item":"edge-cases","status":"fail"},{"item":"doc-impact","status":"pass"}],"findings":[{"id":"external-1","severity":"major","file":"src/super_harness/cli/review.py","line":203,"summary":"Non-participant sources can satisfy the approval threshold","detail":"Source validation checks allowed_sources but not policy.participants. With participants [subagent, external] and an additional configured human source, approvals from subagent and human reach min_independent=2 and emit the milestone even though external was the required assignment. This defeats the deterministic participant contract."},{"id":"external-2","severity":"major","file":"src/super_harness/cli/review.py","line":516,"summary":"Verdict freshness does not validate the prepared target HEAD","detail":"Freshness compares only the in-scope digest, then reviewed_head is copied from the pending bundle. A commit affecting only out-of-scope paths after prepare leaves that digest unchanged, so the verdict is accepted and records an obsolete reviewed_head. Plan-review approvals are even less protected because they do not run this freshness check. Require the prepared target_head to match the accepted committed target before recording evidence."},{"id":"external-3","severity":"major","file":"src/super_harness/cli/review.py","line":691,"summary":"review prepare does not reject an invalid reviewer lifecycle state","detail":"The plan explicitly requires review prepare to fail closed for an invalid reviewer state, but prepare loads policy and compiles immediately without calling the existing reviewer-state validator. It can therefore create authoritative assignments for plan-reviewer or code-reviewer outside their corresponding review state."}]},"reviewed_head":"0d7154b51d1173a1735408035e97e927200f8866"}}
